However, Raheem Sterling's superb solo strike rescued a draw for Liverpool to leave the tie finely poised. 

Mourinho added: 'I think it was a really big game, we played to the top of our potential and Liverpool the same.

'A proper semi-final and a fair result. Liverpool did not deserve to lose, they performed really well. We were in control but with more quality in our passing we could find space and score more goals.

'I am not saying we are the favourites. The semi-final is now one leg.'

